{
  "_note": "Machine-readable projection of the term contract. Holds only the flat `terms[]` list and its meta. Test-data lists (formal pronouns, noun-gender map) live in `services/docs/tests/data/` as TypeScript modules. Doctrine that uses tables for illustration (style conventions, marketing softeners, anti-pattern drift→target pairs, toast conventions, error-message patterns, deCH overrides) lives in the TERMINOLOGY*.md files alongside this JSON. The split: term lookup → here; test inputs → tests/data/; doctrine + reference tables → MD.",
  "_fallbackRules": "Each term entry has a required `en` field. Optional locale fields override: `de_ch` falls back to `de`, which falls back to `en`; `fr` falls back to `en`. A term with only `en` set (no `de`, `fr`, `de_ch`) is used unchanged in every locale — typical of brands, acronyms, code identifiers, and established loanwords (`Workflow`, `Dashboard`, `Webhook`).",
  "_categories": {
    "brand": "Brand and product names (Tale, Convex, OpenRouter, GitHub). Always English everywhere.",
    "acronym": "Initialisms (AI, LLM, API, MCP). Some have native expansions (AI → KI/IA); the abbreviation itself usually stays English.",
    "codeIdentifier": "Environment variables, CLI flags, file paths, API paths, i18n keys, JSON keys. International — never translate. Documented by category; individual identifiers are not enumerated here.",
    "role": "The six platform roles (Owner/Admin/Developer/Editor/Member/Disabled). DE/FR UIs ship translated forms.",
    "feature": "Product features and UI surfaces (Knowledge base, Chat with AI, Canvas, Composer).",
    "knowledgeEntity": "Knowledge-base entity types managed by the user (Customer, Vendor, Product, Document, Folder).",
    "technicalVocab": "Universal tech terms (Token, Prompt, Webhook, Pipeline). Bucket 2 in most cases — kept English in DE/FR.",
    "actionVerb": "Button labels and menu actions (Save, Delete, Edit, Log in).",
    "deploymentVocab": "Install/operate/configure terms (Self-hosted, On-premises, Open source, Zero-downtime).",
    "loanword": "Bucket 2 — established English loanword used unchanged in DE/FR. `de`/`fr` either omitted or equal to `en`.",
    "gitDomain": "Bucket 2a — Git/source-control vocabulary (Pull Request, Merge, Rebase). Stays English in DE/FR. Half-translated forms fail review.",
    "translateBucket": "Bucket 3 — must translate. `de` and `fr` differ from `en`; EN form is rejected in DE/FR prose by `loanword.test.ts`.",
    "abbreviation": "Shorthand forms used in tooltips and tight UI (e.g., z. B., p. ex.). `_note` carries the expansion."
  },
